      <bioghist id="aspace_59bd0b3f69e7e872a0e6013b7e8bbc56">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Cornelius Osgood was born in Winchester, Massachusetts, on March 20, 1905. He attended the University of Chicago, attaining the degree of Ph.B. in 1927 and Ph.D. in 1930. He married Harriett Ellen Keeney on September 25, 1930. The couple had two daughters before Harriett's death in 1962. On December 23, 1963, Osgood remarried, to Soo Sui-ling. Osgood was an ethnologist who worked as curator at various museums throughout the country, including the Yale Peabody Museum. He also authored several books about East Asia.  Cornelius Osgood died on January 6, 1985.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <arrangement id="aspace_ba257ca9b5f9571fbf4084e46d8babd5">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The papers are arranged by the original inventory and additional material.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <custodhist id="aspace_095eed4bd545c9a70c68aa2d246c7a68">
         <head>Custodial History</head>
         <p>Gift of Cornelius Osgood, 1983. Gift of Sui-Ling Osgood, 2011.</p>  
      </custodhist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_b96da0b289aaf82a26b7d85cc272fb88">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The papers consist of chapter drafts of <title render="italic">
               <part>Fallen Leaves</part>
            </title> written by Cornelius Osgood.  The additional material consists of photographs taken by Cornelius Osgood during his career as an ethnologist.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
